  "author_association": "NONE",
  "body": "*Title*: *respect x-envoy-max-retries set to 0, despite if num_policy is NULL*\r\n\r\n*Description*:\r\nA service has set `x-envoy-max-retries` to 0, but noticed retries happening to the upstream service. After debugging, we noticed that the [num_policy in our EDS data was not set.](https://github.com/envoyproxy/data-plane-api/blob/4af3ed0740ce913c62afbe7f74d10f0b3738ec3d/envoy/api/v2/route/route.proto#L807-L810)\r\n\r\nThis created the unexpected result of retries happening, even though a service owner expected there to be none.\r\n\r\nThis is due to the fact that the code takes the [max of either the RetryPolicy value or the header value](https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/21b3e6576260640e74b1d311cdea65bd30c04a3b/source/common/router/retry_state_impl.cc#L85).\r\n\r\nThis seems like [expected behavior](https://www.envoyproxy.io/docs/envoy/latest/configuration/http_filters/router_filter#x-envoy-max-retries) but @mattklein123 believes it is a bug. So filing an issue here so we can start a conversation.\r\n\r\n*Repro steps*:\r\n1. Set `num_policy` RetryPolicy to NULL.\r\n2. Send a request with `x-envoy-max-retries` to 0.\r\n",
